         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility"> ¶ About three years ago I sent specimens of a splendid ¶  ¶ Chloanthes ¶  ¶ to Kew; i.e. Chl. Elderi, with yellow &amp; red flowers. In reality it constitutes a distinct genus = ¶  ¶ Hemiphora ¶  ¶ (frag...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">80.08.00</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To [Joseph Hooker]</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1871-81, f. 288.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The addressee and date have been inferred from the content of J. Hooker to M, 8 November 1880. The other items mentioned in Hooker’s letter are consistent with this fragment having been sent in August 1880 (see M to J. Hooker, 10 August 1880<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and M to J. Hooker, 28 August 1880).</p>
               </note>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>About three years ago I sent specimens of a splendid<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Chloanthes<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to Kew; i.e. Chl. Elderi, with yellow &amp; red flowers. In reality it constitutes a distinct genus =<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Hemiphora<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(fragm. X, 13);<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B78.03.01, p. 13, under<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Chloanthes elderi,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>with a reference to the possibility that it should be designated a new genus. It is listed as<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Hemiphora</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>in B83.03.04, p. 103.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the plant is very beautiful and interesting. Could it find a place in the icones?<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>icones<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">is underlined and marked with a line in the margin.</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>The following text is written in pencil on a piece of paper glued to the back of the letter:</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>'I have attached a memo of F. v M’s wish in the cover of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <hi rend="underline">Chloanthes</hi>
                        </seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>[i.e.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>in the cover of the herbarium folder]<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>—<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>So we shall see when the specimen is laid in — I doubt if his material suffice, if it came by post with our present imperfect draughtsmanship DO' [i.e.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Daniel Oliver].</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS annotation by Oliver on the attached paper: 'Cyperaceae monopolise at present'.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Sir Th. Elder would feel gratified, to see it depicted.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The species was not figured in<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Icones</seg>, but did appear in an uncoloured illustration in<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Engler’s botanische Jahrbucher</seg>, vol. 35 (1904), p. 518. In 1875 Sir Thomas Elder had funded Ernest Giles on an expedition from Port Augusta to Perth (Threadgill, 1922, vol. 1, pp. 153–7). It was on this expedition that J. Young collected the specimens described by M.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Chloanthes Elderi</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Hemiphora</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
